(i) Scope of Non-Confidentiality: The aforementioned obligations concerning confidential information shall not extend to any data that:
   (A) has been publicly disclosed without fault or negligence on the part of the recipient;
   (B) is obtained from a third party who was under no obligation of confidentiality and had no restrictions on its dissemination;
   (C) was already in the possession of the recipient prior to its disclosure by the other party;
   (D) is independently created or developed by the recipient's personnel, who were not previously exposed to similar confidential information from the other party.
